This increase represents a 15.5% positivity rate. As per the National Department of Health, a further 181 COVID-19 related deaths have been reported, bringing total fatalities to 92 830 to date. About 21 654 544 tests have been conducted in both public and private sectors. The majority of new cases today are from Western Cape (28%), followed by Gauteng (22%). Kwa-Zulu Natal accounted for 18%; Eastern Cape accounted for 11%; Limpopo accounted for 5%; Free State, Mpumalanga, Northern Cape and North West each accounted for 4% respectively of today’s new cases. The NICD, a division of the National Health Laboratory Service, continues to provide laboratory-based surveillance to inform the public health response towards COVID-19 in South Africa. --ChannelAfrica-- 181 6 762 21 654 544 3 309 735 3 540 891 12 January 2022 92 830 138 326 3 402 565